:QUOTE
A good coliving space gives you community without the distraction of setting it up yourself.

:INFO
Finding Coliving Spaces for Remote Workers
Coliving combines accommodation and workspace in one monthly package. Quality varies enormously. The best spaces accelerate your network and your work. The worst are overpriced hostels with a standing desk.

:COUNTER.half
800 USD
Average monthly cost in Southeast Asia
|
:COUNTER.half
2500 USD
Average monthly cost in Western Europe

:PATH
Search the Platforms
Use Coliving.com, Outsite, and Nomad List as starting points. Filter by workspace quality, not just photos of common areas. Look for reviews from workers, not vacationers.

:PATH
Evaluate Before Booking
Ask for a video tour of the workspace and internet speed test results. Check upload speed, not just download. Contact current residents directly if the platform allows it.

:PATH
Book Your First Stay
Start with a one or two week stay before committing to a month. Arrive with a clear work schedule so you can assess the space under real conditions, not vacation mode.

:CHECKLIST
Coliving Evaluation Checklist
[ ] Minimum 50 Mbps upload speed confirmed
[ ] Quiet workspace available during core hours
[ ] Kitchen access for meal prep
[ ] Clear house rules posted
[ ] Month-to-month option available
[ ] Reviews from workers not just tourists

:NOTE
The community in a coliving space matters as much as the infrastructure. Ask who else is staying before you book.

